Blocks.childText: TO WORK. WHAT SHALL THE HARVEST BE? Concluded. ter ni ty, Sure, ah, sure will the har vest be. gathered in time or eternity, Sure,ah,yes, will the harvest be, will the harvest, the harvest be. 84 MRS. E. S. OAKEY. Sowing the seed of a tarnished name, 2 Sowing their seed by the way-side high, Sowing the seed of eternal shame- Sowing their seed on the rocks to die, Ah, sure will the harvest be, etc. Sowing their seed where the thorns will spoil, Sowing their seed in the fertile soil, 4 Sowing the seed with an aching heart, Oh, what shall the harvest be, etc. Sowing the seed while the teardrops start, Sowing in hope till the reapers come, 3 Sowing the seed of a lingering pain, Gladly to gather the harvest home, Sowing the seed of a maddened brain, Oh, what shall the harvest be, etc. MISSIONARY HYMN. 7s & 6s. "The Macedonian cry." L. MASON. 1. From Greenland's icy mountains, From India's coral strand, Where Afric's sunny fountains Roll down their golden sand; From many an ancient riv-er, From many a palmy plain, They call us to de - liv- er Their land from error's chain. 85 R. HEBER. 2 What though the spicy breezes 3 Shall we, whose souls are lighted Blow soft o'er Ceylon's isle- By wisdom from on high- Though every prospect pleases, Shall we, to man benighted, And only man is vile! The lamp of life deny? In vain, with lavish kindness, Salvation ! oh, salvation The gifts of God are strewn; The joyful sound proclaim, The heathen, in their blindness, Till earth's remotest nation Bow down to wood and stone. Has learned Messiah's name. 59
